Module mesakit.graph.world
Package com.telenav.mesakit.graph.world

Class WorldGraphIndex

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.mesakit.graph.world.WorldGraphIndex
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.telenav.kivakit.core.registry.RegistryTrait, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.Named, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.NamedObject, Serializable
public class WorldGraphIndex extends Object implements com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.Named, Serializable, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.NamedObject, com.telenav.kivakit.core.registry.RegistryTrait
The world graph index stores metadata and provides spatial indexing services for a WorldGraph which can't easily be composed of the spatial indexes in individual cell graphs.

This class is an implementation detail of the WorldGraph and is only public because it has to be accessed from other packages.

Attributes

A world graph index has metadata describing the contents of the entire world graph. This is accessed with metadata(). The version of the graph index can be retrieved with version().

Persistence

The world graph index for a WorldGraph is stored in the WorldGraphRepositoryFolder that contains the cell graphs. The file containing the index is called "index.world". This file is a FieldArchive stored in zip format where each stream in the zip file stores an object in this index. A world graph index can be loaded from an "index.world" file with loadFrom(File) and it can be saved to such a file with save(File, Metadata).

Places

Since there is a frequent need to query places from many neighboring cells, this is made more efficient with a single spatial index for all places in a world graph. The number of places in this index can be retrieved with placeCount() and queries for places can be conducted with:

  • placesInside(Rectangle) - A sequence of places inside the given bounds
  • placeForLocation(Location) - The place (if any) at the given location

Ways

It would be time-consuming to search all cells in the world graph for a way identifier, so this index provides the worldCellForWayIdentifier(WorldGrid, MapWayIdentifier) method to find one arbitrary cell containing a given way identifier. Any other cells that contain the way identifier can be found by navigating the way starting within the given cell.
